fields.title: Why Michaelism and More Said Preluding My Original WordPress Blog
fields.preface: I started my WordPress blog on December, 2014 and this blog post was its intro and my first attempt on gibberish style. I pretty much abandoned the WordPress blog because one, the management panel is just too inflexible for my whimsical needs, two, WordPress is blocked in China.
fields.abstract: I felt extremely free chunking out these texts. This resulted a very chaotic intro to my short-living WordPress blog.

fields.title: 迷失东京 ー 最熟悉的陌生感
fields.preface: 本文原题为“生存报告 Vol.1 (迷失东京)”。生存报告这个词其实是从Facebook好友やぁはん那里学来的，这第一期谈的就是一个暑假在日本东京学习生活的见闻。The English title has been added later, the oxymoron is intended to convey the deeply rooted sense of paradox that I experienced in Japanese culture and society.
fields.abstract: 最守规则的国家，人们会想到日本；变态最多的国家，人们估计也会想到日本。我觉得日本是一个极端矛盾的国家，但或许，这只是某种个体现象聚群而得以放大罢了。

fields.title: 東京での迷い（東京生活感想）
fields.abstract: 日本は矛盾の社会なのか？３ヶ月日本で生活する間、この矛盾性を実感して、読み解いてみた。14年夏、東京生活の感想をお届けします。

fields.title: Your Birth Package - Birthright Citizenship and Global Inequality
fields.preface: This essay was my final research paper for Stanford writing class "PWR2: Speaking Out: Claiming Citizenship, Demanding Rights.". As an international student in United States, I am tightly bounded by the US immigration laws, through which I clearly feel the inequality between citizenship holders from different countries. This research entitled me a more methodological approach to understanding the essence and function of citizenship.
fields.abstract: The legitimacy of birthright citizenship might be justifying an indeed sinister tool to demarcate global population and perpetuate global inequality.

fields.title: Determinism and Moral Responsiblity
fields.preface: Whether determinism is compatible with moral responsibility is a central question for the philosophy of free will. In common-sense interpretation, determinism means a person's behaviors are decided by some factors beyond himself (like he is coerced to kill someone) and determinism usually exempts a person from moral responsibility (his penalty is far less than that of an intentional murderer because he committed the crime in opposed to his own free will). However, the actual philosophical debates between determinism and moral responsibility extend beyond where one's intuition can easily reach. This essay analyzes contradictory views of two famous philosophers Harry Frankfurt and Derk Pereboom on this topic.
fields.abstract: If everything, including human's mind is deterministic by physical laws, will a person still hold moral responsibility for what he did? I analyzed arguments from two different philosophers in this article.

fields.title: A Three-Dimensional Inquiry into Personal Identity
fields.abstract: We seem never to question the continuation of our identity, namely the fact that I am the person I was in the past. But why? What speaks for this continuity.

fields.title: Lightweight Layout Engine For UIViews
fields.abstract: A tutorial to use MHLayoutView, a tool I designed to easily lay out views of iOS applications, for folks that prefer code to interface builders.

fields.title: Notches on the Wall
fields.preface: Personal statement for my college application.
fields.abstract: My grandpa marked my height on a wall every time I visited him during my childhood. In retrospect, these notches represent much more than a mere record of my growth.

fields.title: 后APP时代的“圈地运动”与渡鸦科技的“土地改革”
fields.preface: RavenTech is a tech startup located in Beijing that has a very unique product and a believe-it-or-not iconoclastic company culture. This essay is my afterthoughts of the speech given by CHENG LV, RevenTech's cofounder and CEO, during Zhen Residence (真驿站).
fields.abstract: 渡鸦科技做的不仅仅是人工智能和用户需求的整合，它的愿景将是更彻底的颠覆和未来完全不同的人机交互模式。

fields.title: J.J. Thomson on Abortion
fields.preface: This essay is based on J.J. Thomson's arguments made in his famous paper A Defense of Abortion published in 1971. I agree with his position on general permissibility of abortion.
fields.abstract: It seems not reasonable for one person to rely on another person's body for survival. Using someone else's possession is an action of stealing, let alone using someone else's body. However, this argument becomes much more intricate regarding abortion.

fields.title: Should pornography be censored?
fields.abstract: Pornography and censorship is among the most contestable issues of feminism. The historical arguments lay between the conservatives who deem pornography as obscene and corrupting and the liberals who firmly defend the freedom of speech. The new waves of feminist movements bring new perspectives into this century-long debate.

fields.title: The Resolute – UK and the Eurozone
fields.abstract: The struggles between the UK and a uniform economic system of the European continent tell a thrilling, if not disappointing, story. I was wondering why UK did not join the Eurozone throughout my exchange term at Oxford, until I finally did my research on this topic and found all these fascinating reasons that intertwine behind UK's resolute standing outside the Eurozone.

fields.title: LINEの既読機能を廃止すべきか
fields.abstract: ご存知のとおり、LINEは既読通知という機能がついている。しかし、この機能のつながる誤解やいじめが起きやすいというクレームもよく入っている。既読機能の存続について、ここで少し考えてみよう。

fields.title: Meaning and Reference of Natural Kinds
fields.preface: This essay is the second one for my eight-week-long tutorial on Philosophy of Mind and Epistemology at University of Oxford when I exchanged there Winter Quarter, 2016. It is a relatively easy one for anyone without relevant background.
fields.abstract: What do we mean and what specifically do we refer to when we say “water”, "tiger", or "lemon"? The problem of reference is a seemingly commonsensical but actually quite interesting metalinguistic topic. Philosopher Saul Kripke and Hilary Putnam offer brilliantly new theories that challenged our traditional understanding of "meaning".
